---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
---

<Base title="About" description="Learn about the Atmosphere community and AT Protocol.">
  <Header slot="header" />

  <article class="about-page section">
    <div class="container container--narrow">
      <h1>About the Atmosphere</h1>

      <div class="prose">
        <p>
          The <strong>Atmosphere</strong> is the growing community of people and projects building on
          <a href="https://atproto.com" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank">AT Protocol</a> — the
          open, decentralized protocol behind <a href="https://bsky.app" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank">Bluesky</a>
          and a growing ecosystem of apps, tools, and services.
        </p>

        <p>
          atmosphere.community is the community front door. We aggregate blog posts from
          <a href="https://blog.atmosphere.community" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank">our Offprint blog</a>,
          surface upcoming events from <a href="https://smokesignal.events" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank">Smoke Signal</a>,
          and connect you with local AT Protocol communities around the world.
        </p>

        <h2>AT Protocol</h2>
        <p>
          AT Protocol (Authenticated Transfer Protocol) is an open standard for building social applications.
          It gives users control over their identity, data, and social connections — so you can move between
          apps without starting over.
        </p>
        <p>
          Your <strong>Atmosphere account</strong> is your identity across the ecosystem. It's portable — you own
          your handle, your data, and your social graph. Apps built on AT Protocol interoperate, meaning your
          posts, follows, and interactions work across the entire Atmosphere.
        </p>

        <h2>Community Fund</h2>
        <p>
          The <a href="https://opencollective.com/atprotocoldev/" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank">AT Protocol Community Fund</a>
          supports projects, events, and infrastructure that strengthen the ecosystem. It has funded community
          conferences, developer tools, and educational resources.
        </p>

        <h2>Get involved</h2>
        <p>There are many ways to participate in the Atmosphere community:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>
            <a href="https://blog.atmosphere.community" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank">Subscribe to the newsletter</a>
            — email updates or follow via Bluesky
          </li>
          <li>
            <a href="https://discourse.atprotocol.community" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank">Join the Discourse forum</a>
            — discussions, proposals, and community coordination
          </li>
          <li>
            <a href="https://github.com/ATProtocol-Community" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank">Contribute on GitHub</a>
            — open-source projects and community infrastructure
          </li>
          <li>
            <a href="https://bsky.app/profile/atmosphere.community" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank">Follow on Bluesky</a>
            — <code>@atmosphere.community</code>
          </li>
          <li>
            <a href={`${import.meta.env.BASE_URL}/communities`}>Find a local community</a> near you
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </article>

  <Footer slot="footer" />
</Base>

<style>
  .about-page h1 {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-xl);
  }

  .prose {
    font-size: var(--text-base);
    line-height: var(--leading-relaxed);
    max-width: 65ch;
  }

  .prose h2 {
    margin-top: var(--space-2xl);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-md);
  }

  .prose p + p {
    margin-top: var(--space-base);
  }

  .prose ul {
    margin-top: var(--space-base);
    padding-left: var(--space-lg);
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: var(--space-sm);
  }

  .prose li {
    line-height: var(--leading-relaxed);
  }

  .prose code {
    font-size: 0.9em;
    background: var(--neutral-100);
    padding: 2px 6px;
    border-radius: var(--radius-sm);
  }

  .prose strong {
    font-weight: 600;
  }
</style>
